Interface ReversibleIterator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, java.io.Closeable, SequenceIterator
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConstrainedIterator<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmptyIterator, GroupByIterator.ManualGroupByIterator, ListIterator, ListIterator.Atomic, ListIterator.OfNodes, ManualGroupIterator, ManualIterator, ManualRegexIterator, MergeGroupingIterator.ManualMergeGroupingIterator, RangeIterator, ReverseListIterator, ReverseRangeIterator, SingleAtomicIterator, SingleNodeIterator, SingletonIterator

    public interface ReversibleIterator
extends SequenceIterator
    A ReversibleIterator is an interface implemented by any SequenceIterator that is able to deliver items in reverse order (or to supply another iterator that can do so).
